  {
    "title": "Lore",
    "depth": 1,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Irithel was abandoned in the jungle by her parents when she was a little girl."
          },
          {
            "text": "Under the guidance of the God of Jungle, a female smilodon that had just given birth adopted her."
          },
          {
            "text": "Being protected by the mother smilodon, the little smilodon Leo and Irithel learned to hunt, survive, and grew up like an animal."
          },
          {
            "text": "During a territory fight, the mother smilodon was badly injured."
          },
          {
            "text": "When Irithel and her \"brother\" Leo went to a town for help, they were captured as \"smilodon children\" by a slaveholder."
          },
          {
            "text": "When the cat elf mage - Nana - passed by and couldn't watch them get beaten to death, she suddenly had the super power inside her that allowed her to save these two poor children.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Nana"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "With the help of Nana, Irithel was able to understand human languages and combat skills while Leo grew up to become a strong adult smilodon."
          },
          {
            "text": "But Irithel still hates humans and trusts her only friend - Leo."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
