    ],
    "lists": [
      [
        {
          "text": "The name Irithel is of Turkish origin and means \"Goddess of hunt and pray. Strong bow and arch\"."
        },
        {
          "text": "When Irithel was first released she was called Mona and hero title \"Descendant of the Forest.\""
        },
        {
          "text": "Irithel is the first rider heroes."
        },
        {
          "text": "Irithel referred Leo as a \"tiger\" in one of her quotes, but he is biologically a smilodon."
        },
        {
          "text": "Irithel is the first hero who can do Basic Attacks while moving."
        },
        {
          "text": "Irithel is the only ranged hero with an explosive Basic Attack, where the damage of her Basic Attack during can hit multiple enemies in a small AoE at once."
        },
        {
          "text": "She is also the first and the only hero that have and has a unique background."
        },
        {
          "text": "Currently, she is also the hero that has never been remodel since her release and is still using the same model without any changes."
        },
        {
          "text": "When her \"Night Arrow\" skin was released, Leo's appearance closely resembled Toothless from How To Train Your Dragon; it was later changed to have a more feline look, likely to avoid copyright issues.",
          "links": [
            {
              "type": "interwiki",
              "wiki": "wikipedia",
              "page": "How To Train Your Dragon"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "She is the fourth hero to have two StarLight skins (\"Nightarrow\" and \"Checkered Knight\").",
          "links": [
            {
              "text": "StarLight",
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "StarLight Member"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    ]
  }
